NEW YORK - Fashion designer Kate Spade was found dead in her New York flat by her housekeeper on Tuesday, authorities said. It's alleged that the 55-year-old designer hanged herself. Officials at the scene confirmed that she left a note, though the contents are not yet known. READ: Local designer takes on Zara over 'copyright infringement' Spade began her career in the 1980s working for women's magazine ‘Mademoiselle’ in Manhattan. In 1993 she launched Kate Spade Handbags which later blossomed into a full-scale clothing and jewellery line. eNCA